  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6599.48 sitting between the max negative gamma wall at 6590 (-13.9B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+20.8B), dealers are in active hedging mode as spot approaches the critical 6605 resistance where they'll aggressively sell into any push higher. The massive GEX surge (416% in 5 minutes) indicates heavy options flow is forcing dealers to rapidly adjust hedges, creating the current PIN regime that should cap upside momentum near 6605 and provide strong support at 6590. Key levels to watch: 6590 downside support where dealer buying accelerates, 6605-6610 resistance zone where dealer selling intensifies, and the 6622 flip point where the entire hedging dynamic reverses.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect price to get pinned between 6590 and 6605 with dealers fighting moves in either direction.",
